Created attachment 1137506 Differences between virt-manager-qt4 and virt-manager-qt5
Description of problem: Qt4 apps seems to miss the icons related to the menu's items
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): adwaita-qt-common-0.3-2.fc24.noarch adwaita-qt4-0.3-2.fc24.x86_64 adwaita-qt-0.3-2.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible: Always (tried virt-manager-qt4 and q4wine)
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Open a Qt4 App 2. Navigate through its main menu
Actual results: 1. Menu's items haven't got any icon.
Expected results: 1. Menu's items should have items.
Additional info: I'm attaching a screenshots which compares virt-manager-qt4 with virt-manager-qt5

Hello, I got the same problem, but with other and serveral applications. In Zim Desktop app, Pidgin, and many other apps miss the menu icons. I checked the box in "gconf-editor" desktop > gnome > interface > menus have icons and restarted the gnome session and also restarted the PC, still no way!
I upgraded from Fedora 23 > Fedora 24 then to Fedora 25 juste right after.
The thing is, I tried to log in with Gnome classic, or Gnome with Xorg, i didn't have this bug, it seems to be related to Wayland ? Any information to debug this is appreciated.
thanks
